  • Classes in com.davidsoergel.trees used by com.davidsoergel.trees 
    Class and Description
    AbstractHierarchyNode
    Abstract implementation of some of the most basic HierarchyNode functionality.
    AbstractRootedPhylogeny
    Abstract implementation of the RootedPhylogeny interface, providing all required functionality that is not implementation-specific.
    AbstractRootedPhylogeny.MutualExclusionResolutionMode
    When we request extraction of a tree with a bunch of nodes, and one of those nodes is an ancestor of the other, do we include only the leaf, only the ancestor, both, or throw an exception? BOTHNOBRANCHLENGTH is a compromise between ANCESTOR and BOTH; both nodes are provided, but all branch lengths below the ancestor are set to zero.
    BasicPhylogenyNode
    A basic implementation of the PhylogenyNode interface, where the generic type indicates the type of node IDs that are used (typically Strings or Integers).
    BasicRootedPhylogeny
    Really this wants to extend BasicPhylogenyNode, but we can't (multiple inheritance, etc.), so we just facade a root node for many methods.
    DepthFirstTreeIterator
    An Iterator that provides all of the nodes of a tree in depth-first order.
    HierarchicalStringObjectMap
    A node in a simple hierarchy, where a Map from Strings to Objects is attached at each node.
    HierarchyNode
    A node in a simple hierarchy, where a value of the given generic type is attached at each node.
    ImmutableHierarchyNode 
    ImmutableSortedSetHierarchyNode

    NoSuchNodeException

    RootedPhylogeny
